{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 18:15:47.519685", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary\n- Overall network is partially healthy: the 10.1.1.0/24 user segment reaches DNS and the web farm (including the load balancer), but the 10.2.1.0/24 user segment appears isolated.\n- A hard failure exists for 10.2.1.0/24 due to DHCP failure and lack of routing adjacency at the distribution layer.\n- Additional latent misconfiguration is present on both distribution routers regarding DHCP relay.\n\nObserved Reachability and Symptoms\n- Host in 10.1.1.0/24 (host_1_1_1_1):\n  - Has a DHCP-assigned IP 10.1.1.10/24 with default route 10.1.1.1.\n  - Can ping DNS (10.200.0.2) and the load balancer (10.200.0.7).\n  - curl to http://web99.local succeeds with normal timing; DNS resolution functions (resolv.conf points to 10.200.0.2).\n- Host in 10.2.1.0/24 (host_2_1_1_1):\n  - No IPv4 address on eth0; no default route.\n  - Pings to DNS, load balancer, and even the local default gateway are “Network is unreachable.”\n  - curl to http://web99.local yields zero/empty timing (no connectivity).\n- Global reachability sample:\n  - Server farm components (load_balancer, web_server_0–3, dns_server) can reach 10.1.1.10 with normal RTTs.\n  - Many 10.2.x hosts show “unknown” or failures in the automated matrix, consistent with the 10.2.1.0/24 segment being down.\n\nFault Localization\n- Distribution router for the failing segment (router_dist_2_1):\n  - L3 SVI/bridge br0 is up with 10.2.1.1/24, so the local gateway IP is present.\n  - OSPF adjacency is not established: “show ip ospf neighbor” shows no neighbors. “show ip route” contains only connected routes; no routes to server farm (10.200.0.0/24) or elsewhere.\n  - As a result, router_dist_2_1 cannot reach the DHCP server (10.200.0.8): ping returns “Network is unreachable.”\n  - DHCP relay service is inactive and unconfigured:\n    - isc-dhcp-relay status: inactive (dead).\n    - /etc/default/isc-dhcp-relay has empty SERVERS and INTERFACES.\n- Core involved in this adjacency (router_core_2):\n  - Interfaces are up, correct addressing on eth2 (172.16.0.10/31) toward router_dist_2_1 (172.16.0.11/31).\n  - OSPF process configured to include 172.16.0.10/31 in area 1, but “show ip ospf neighbor” shows no neighbors (no adjacency).\n- Distribution router for the healthy segment (router_dist_1_1):\n  - OSPF adjacency present (neighbor over 172.16.0.6); routes to 10.200.0.0/24 learned via OSPF.\n  - Can ping the DHCP server (10.200.0.8).\n  - However, DHCP relay is also inactive and unconfigured here (service inactive; SERVERS/INTERFACES empty). Despite this, existing 10.1.1.10 host already has a lease; renewal may fail later without a working relay.\n\nRoot Cause Analysis\n- Primary cause of outage in 10.2.1.0/24:\n  1) DHCP relay on router_dist_2_1 is not running and not configured (no SERVERS/INTERFACES). This prevents host_2_1_1_1 from obtaining an IP address from the central DHCP server.\n  2) Concurrently, OSPF adjacency between router_dist_2_1 (172.16.0.11/31) and router_core_2 (172.16.0.10/31) is down. Without this adjacency, router_dist_2_1 has no route to 10.200.0.0/24, so even a functioning relay would be unable to forward requests to the DHCP server. This also isolates the segment from the rest of the network.\n- Secondary/latent issues:\n  - DHCP relay is also inactive and unconfigured on router_dist_1_1. The currently healthy 10.1.1.0/24 segment likely relies on an existing lease; DHCP renewals or new clients on this segment may fail.\n\nEvidence Highlights\n- host_2_1_1_1: eth0 has no IPv4; ip route empty; pings return “Network is unreachable”; curl shows no connectivity.\n- router_dist_2_1: show ip ospf neighbor empty; show ip route lacks routes beyond connected; ping to 10.200.0.8 fails with “Network is unreachable”; isc-dhcp-relay inactive; /etc/default/isc-dhcp-relay empty.\n- router_core_2: OSPF configured for the link to router_dist_2_1, but no neighbors seen.\n- router_dist_1_1: OSPF adjacency up; routes to server farm present; can ping DHCP server; but isc-dhcp-relay inactive and unconfigured.\n- host_1_1_1_1: DHCP-assigned address, DNS reachable, web99.local accessible.\n\nImpact\n- All hosts in 10.2.1.0/24 are unable to obtain addresses and are effectively offline from the enterprise network and server farm.\n- 10.1.1.0/24 functions now but has a latent DHCP relay misconfiguration that risks future lease renewals and onboarding of new clients.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 16813, "output_tokens": 4838, "total_tokens": 21651, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 14592}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3584}}}
